You Are:

You are a dedicated engineer with a background in electronic engineering, eager to learn and explore new technologies. Your problem-solving skills and proficiency in UNIX/Linux and programming languages make you a valuable team player. With 2+ years of experience, you are familiar with VLSI EDA tools and have hands-on experience in IC design.

What You’ll Be Doing:

Design, develop, troubleshoot, or debug software tools for integrated circuits.
Support a global design team and debug flow and design issues.
Develop routines and utility programs for IC design.
Build productive working relationships.
Produce technical documentation.
Integrate new solutions into existing processes.
The Impact You Will Have:

Drive the design and verification of high-performance silicon chips.
Enhance the efficiency of a global design team.
Integrate new technologies into design flows.
Ensure reliability of integrated circuits.
Foster collaboration and knowledge sharing.
Contribute to innovative solutions in electronic design automation.
What You’ll Need:

Bachelor's or Master's degree in Electronic Engineering.
At least 4+ years of experience in Layout design, CAD
Desire to learn new technologies.
Good analysis and problem-solving skills.
UNIX/Linux knowledge.
Proficiency in a programming language.
Technical documentation skills.
Good communication skills in English.
Who You Are:

Collaborative and team-oriented.
Detail-oriented and multitasking.
Adaptable and proactive.
Committed to continuous learning.
